WEBVTT

00:03.880 --> 00:05.210
Previously on "How to
Get Away with Murder"...
Annalise: No!

00:05.210 --> 00:06.750
Annalise:
My mother has dementia.

00:06.750 --> 00:09.000
I'll tell them
you didn't burn down the house.

00:09.000 --> 00:09.830
I did.

00:09.830 --> 00:11.120
She has episodes.

00:11.120 --> 00:13.710
Connor, marry me.
I mean it.

00:13.710 --> 00:15.080
Dr. Huang:
There's the heartbeat.

00:15.080 --> 00:16.540
How much time do I have?

00:16.540 --> 00:17.920
24 weeks.

00:17.920 --> 00:19.710
We have to give Denver
another suspect.

00:19.710 --> 00:21.290
Who is it?
Wes?

00:21.290 --> 00:22.380
It's the only way,
Laurel.

00:22.380 --> 00:23.920
I'm not gonna let you
do that.

00:23.920 --> 00:25.210
Annalise:
Wes killed my husband.

00:25.210 --> 00:27.580
He confessed to it on the
voicemail he left that night.

00:27.580 --> 00:29.170
Wes: You can't go down
for what I did.

00:29.170 --> 00:31.710
Denver: This points to Gibbins
being behind both the murders.

00:31.710 --> 00:34.500
I can't continue
to prosecute her

00:34.500 --> 00:37.120
now that Mr. Lahey's
brought me this voicemail.

00:37.120 --> 00:38.830
Laurel: Hey, the guy
who killed Wes is outside,

00:38.830 --> 00:40.710
and we have a chance
to finally confront him!

00:40.710 --> 00:42.620
Laurel!
Dominick?

00:42.620 --> 00:44.040
It's me.

00:44.040 --> 00:45.380
Tell me he's dead.

00:45.380 --> 00:47.120
Yeah.

00:47.120 --> 00:48.830
Annalise: I lost someone.

00:48.830 --> 00:52.500
[ Sobbing ] He felt like my son
because he was my son.

00:52.500 --> 00:53.540
And he's gone.

00:53.540 --> 00:55.500
[ Sniffles ]

00:55.500 --> 00:56.540
[ Sobs ]

00:56.540 --> 01:01.620
♪♪

01:01.620 --> 01:06.920
Annalise: To Michaela,
Connor, Laurel, Asher.

01:06.920 --> 01:10.500
I booked a table at Haywood
at 8:00 tomorrow night.

01:10.500 --> 01:12.790
I need you all there.

01:12.790 --> 01:15.620
Please come.

01:20.250 --> 01:22.500
Jorge: Do I need to take
your phone away?

01:22.500 --> 01:25.330
Or is ignoring your father
just a part of the campus tour?

01:25.330 --> 01:27.920
Sorry.
Are you hungry?

01:27.920 --> 01:30.290
There's a really good café
down the street.

01:30.290 --> 01:32.380
I'd rather see
your apartment.

01:32.380 --> 01:33.420
It's a mess.

01:33.420 --> 01:35.670
I had the jet stop over
to visit you.

01:35.670 --> 01:37.210
I get to see
where you live.

01:37.210 --> 01:39.080
No, not
when I'm still mad at you.

01:39.080 --> 01:40.830
Aw, what'd I do now?

01:40.830 --> 01:42.380
You lied to me.

01:42.380 --> 01:43.880
You're still lying.

01:43.880 --> 01:45.420
How?

01:45.420 --> 01:47.710
When I bumped into Dominick
in New York,

01:47.710 --> 01:49.460
he said
he was there for work.

01:49.460 --> 01:51.620
Because you weren't calling me
back, again.

01:51.620 --> 01:55.000
I knew Dominick
would convince you to see me.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.750
Is that
the only reason why?

01:56.750 --> 01:59.120
Yes.
Mm-hmm.

02:01.250 --> 02:04.330
[ Sighs ]

02:04.330 --> 02:06.420
What other reason
would there be?

02:08.540 --> 02:13.830
♪♪

02:13.830 --> 02:16.620
What is it?

02:16.620 --> 02:18.210
M'ija.

02:20.540 --> 02:23.580
There's a reason why
I wasn't calling you back.

02:27.170 --> 02:29.880
I found out
I was pregnant.

02:32.790 --> 02:36.670
Okay. That's...

02:36.670 --> 02:37.500
Is it Frank's?

02:37.500 --> 02:45.080
♪♪

02:45.080 --> 02:49.000
Laurel, this is a huge thing
you're telling me.

02:49.000 --> 02:52.250
It was a huge thing.

02:52.250 --> 02:54.080
I had an abortion.

02:57.040 --> 02:59.250
Please don't tell Mom.

02:59.250 --> 03:02.250
She's gonna
get all Catholic on me,

03:02.250 --> 03:04.290
and I can't take
any more drama right now.

03:04.290 --> 03:08.460
I won't say anything.
How are you?

03:08.460 --> 03:10.120
Look at me.

03:10.120 --> 03:11.250
Are you okay?

03:11.250 --> 03:13.170
Because
that's all that matters.

03:13.170 --> 03:16.080
M'ija.

03:19.330 --> 03:22.710
Yeah, I'm fine.

03:22.710 --> 03:26.000
Come here.
Can we go eat now?

03:26.000 --> 03:29.170
My apartment is really --
It's not that interesting.

03:29.170 --> 03:33.380
Fine.
But we need a picture.

03:33.380 --> 03:35.460
Excuse me, miss,
could I bother you?

03:35.460 --> 03:40.290
I, um, I'd love a photo
with my lovely daughter here.

03:40.290 --> 03:45.920
♪♪

03:45.920 --> 03:47.500
Cheese.

03:47.500 --> 03:49.000
[ Cellphone camera shutter
clicks ]

03:49.000 --> 03:50.580
Thank you.

03:50.580 --> 03:56.790
♪♪

03:56.790 --> 04:03.380
♪♪

04:03.380 --> 04:05.290
Laurel: I'm meeting a group
for dinner.

04:05.290 --> 04:07.080
The reservation's under
Annalise Keating.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.580
Follow me.

04:08.580 --> 04:15.250
♪♪

04:15.250 --> 04:17.290
Hey.
Sorry I'm late.

04:17.290 --> 04:20.920
My Uber driver
put in the wrong address.

04:20.920 --> 04:22.000
What's this?

04:22.000 --> 04:23.710
She won't tell us.

04:23.710 --> 04:25.540
I'll tell you,
but we should order first.

04:25.540 --> 04:27.210
Sit.

04:27.210 --> 04:35.750
♪♪

04:43.460 --> 04:46.210
Desmond:
You're judging me.

04:46.210 --> 04:50.620
I'll buy you one so I'm not the
only degenerate on the plane.

04:50.620 --> 04:52.420
I'm good.

04:52.420 --> 04:54.670
Probably for the best.

04:54.670 --> 04:56.290
I wouldn't want
to corrupt you.

04:56.290 --> 04:59.250
Any good gossip?
[ Inhales deeply ]

04:59.250 --> 05:01.790
Sorry, I talk a lot.

05:01.790 --> 05:05.210
I just know I'd kick myself
later if I didn't at least try.

05:11.120 --> 05:12.500
Desmond.

05:12.500 --> 05:14.750
Bonnie.

05:14.750 --> 05:16.540
I had
a Great Aunt Bonnie.

05:16.540 --> 05:18.620
Know what
her last words to me were?

05:18.620 --> 05:20.620
"Shut your trap, Desmond."

05:20.620 --> 05:22.830
Too bad for you I still
haven't learned my lesson.

05:22.830 --> 05:24.250
No, you haven't.

05:24.250 --> 05:25.960
Not one bit.

05:25.960 --> 05:28.710
[ Both laugh ]

05:28.710 --> 05:30.620
Woman: Ladies and gentlemen,
we have just begun

05:30.620 --> 05:32.540
our final descent
into Memphis.

05:32.540 --> 05:34.380
At this time,
we kindly request

05:34.380 --> 05:36.540
you return your seats
and tray tables

05:36.540 --> 05:39.120
to their upright position.

05:39.120 --> 05:40.880
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

05:44.460 --> 05:46.460
Celestine:
Oh, right on time!

05:46.460 --> 05:48.750
I guess TSA wasn't screening
for ex-cons.

05:48.750 --> 05:50.210
Kiss my ass.

05:50.210 --> 05:51.830
[ Both laugh ]

05:51.830 --> 05:54.670
What, are we selling liquor
from the back of the house now?

05:54.670 --> 05:57.120
That's his idea
of a solution.

05:57.120 --> 05:59.540
Anna Mae, Anna Mae.

05:59.540 --> 06:02.580
Oh, Mama.
[ Laughs ]

06:05.120 --> 06:07.750
Girl, you used to have
a shelf booty.

06:07.750 --> 06:09.290
Can't put nothing on that
now.

06:09.290 --> 06:11.620
[ Laughs ]
Let's eat. [ Laughs ]

06:11.620 --> 06:14.080
Mac: You could always use
the money to buy a new house.

06:14.080 --> 06:15.960
Thelonius has
that construction experience.

06:15.960 --> 06:17.580
I bet he'd help.

06:17.580 --> 06:20.830
Thelonius is in Atlanta thinking
he's gonna invent an app.

06:20.830 --> 06:23.620
How much money is the insurance
company giving you anyway?

06:23.620 --> 06:25.500
It's enough.

06:25.500 --> 06:27.920
Well, are we talking Oprah money
or Gayle money?

06:27.920 --> 06:29.120
Don't answer that.

06:29.120 --> 06:30.880
Otherwise the whole town
will be rushing over here

06:30.880 --> 06:31.920
with their hands out.

06:31.920 --> 06:34.540
Well, you'll be the first one
in line.

06:34.540 --> 06:38.670
Well, whatever you do,
I hope you use some of it

06:38.670 --> 06:40.710
to get yourself
a proper office.

06:40.710 --> 06:43.000
Actually, Mama --

06:43.000 --> 06:44.830
And hire Nathaniel too.

06:44.830 --> 06:48.920
Wouldn't hurt
to have a pretty secretary.

06:48.920 --> 06:50.960
[ Laughter ]
Mama...

06:50.960 --> 06:52.290
Mama, listen.

06:57.580 --> 06:59.420
What's wrong?

06:59.420 --> 07:02.420
There's a Memory Care Center
in Harbor Town, Mama.

07:02.420 --> 07:04.500
And now that I have
some extra money,

07:04.500 --> 07:07.620
we thought
that we could...

07:07.620 --> 07:09.500
take a look.

07:09.500 --> 07:12.080
Mac:
Is this really necessary?

07:12.080 --> 07:14.710
Your mother and I are getting
along real good here.

07:14.710 --> 07:15.830
According to who?

07:15.830 --> 07:16.920
She wandered over
to Miss Francine's house

07:16.920 --> 07:18.000
in the middle of the night.

07:18.000 --> 07:19.290
She could've gotten shot.

07:19.290 --> 07:21.170
I took care of that.

07:21.170 --> 07:25.460
You put a bell
on the door.

07:25.460 --> 07:29.290
Now, Mama, I'm not saying
that you have to go.

07:29.290 --> 07:32.710
Just that we should visit
while I'm here.

07:32.710 --> 07:35.210
Stop it.

07:35.210 --> 07:37.960
How dare you?

07:37.960 --> 07:41.500
Getting me all excited because
I think you've come to see me.

07:41.500 --> 07:43.830
This was my idea
as much as Anna Mae's, Mama.

07:43.830 --> 07:46.120
Now that we're
back in each other's lives...

07:49.170 --> 07:52.250
...you think I'm gonna be
a burden to you, is that it?

07:52.250 --> 07:54.170
You'd rather pick out
my tombstone.

07:54.170 --> 07:56.250
This is for your safety,
Mama.

07:56.250 --> 07:58.960
The hell do you know
about safety?

07:58.960 --> 08:00.580
Hmm?

08:00.580 --> 08:04.540
You've got people dying
all around you every day!

08:04.540 --> 08:08.330
And you're gonna tell me
how to live?

08:08.330 --> 08:11.120
If that's your idea
of Mama love,

08:11.120 --> 08:14.210
I don't need it.

08:14.210 --> 08:16.460
Don't come back here
no more.

08:16.460 --> 08:25.670
♪♪

08:25.670 --> 08:27.460
[ Knock on door ]

08:27.460 --> 08:28.710
Annalise: Mama,
please open the door.

08:33.080 --> 08:36.500
I made some cobbler from the
pears you left in the kitchen.

08:36.500 --> 08:39.120
I can't promise there'll be
anything left in the morning.

08:45.790 --> 08:47.040
[ Cellphone rings ]

08:50.210 --> 08:52.210
Hi.
Bonnie: How's it going?

08:52.210 --> 08:53.120
Terrible.

08:53.120 --> 08:55.040
Did the Bar
postpone my hearing?

08:55.040 --> 08:57.420
No. It's about
the insurance money.

08:57.420 --> 08:59.710
They're freezing
the payment.
Why?

08:59.710 --> 09:02.420
Hannah Keating is contesting
your ownership of the house,

09:02.420 --> 09:04.670
claiming the insurance money
should go to her.

09:04.670 --> 09:06.540
I'll file a Petition
for Declaratory Judgment

09:06.540 --> 09:07.670
to get the funds released,

09:07.670 --> 09:09.170
but it's going to take
a few months.

09:09.170 --> 09:10.880
[ Knock on door ]

09:10.880 --> 09:11.960
Mac: Anna Mae?

09:11.960 --> 09:12.960
I'll call you back.

09:17.330 --> 09:19.210
You feel like a little nightcap
on the porch?

09:19.210 --> 09:20.210
I'm tired.

09:20.210 --> 09:22.880
Well, you know
where to find me.

09:22.880 --> 09:29.710
♪♪

09:29.710 --> 09:36.250
♪♪

09:36.250 --> 09:38.790
[ Breathing heavily ]

09:38.790 --> 09:47.710
♪♪

09:47.710 --> 09:56.380
♪♪

09:56.380 --> 10:05.080
♪♪

10:05.080 --> 10:13.750
♪♪

10:13.750 --> 10:22.670
♪♪

10:22.670 --> 10:24.460
[ Television playing ]

10:24.460 --> 10:25.830
Where are you headed?

10:25.830 --> 10:29.420
Celestine's.

10:29.420 --> 10:31.580
[ Grunts ]
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

10:31.580 --> 10:41.000
♪♪

10:41.000 --> 10:42.380
Desmond: Bonnie.

10:42.380 --> 10:44.670
Annalise: [ Exhales ]

10:44.670 --> 10:46.670
I'm still a little stunned
you called.

10:46.670 --> 10:48.210
Yeah, me too.

10:48.210 --> 10:51.210
Well, I got us a couple of spots
at the bar.

10:51.210 --> 10:53.250
They're known
for their martinis.

10:53.250 --> 10:55.920
[ Sighs ]

10:55.920 --> 10:58.710
I'm not here to drink.

11:04.880 --> 11:07.670
[ Indistinct shouting,
dance music playing ]

11:10.670 --> 11:12.580
-Come dance with the bride!
-No.

11:12.580 --> 11:13.920
She has to dance
with a guy in a red shirt.

11:13.920 --> 11:15.290
You're in a red shirt.

11:15.290 --> 11:18.170
First of all, this is a gay bar,
not a zoo attraction.

11:18.170 --> 11:19.420
Harvey Milk didn't die

11:19.420 --> 11:21.790
so that you could suck face
with strippers.

11:21.790 --> 11:25.250
Who died?
Uh, w-why don't you go
buy us some drinks

11:25.250 --> 11:26.500
and then
maybe we'll dance with you.

11:26.500 --> 11:29.120
-Yas Qween?
-Yaassss, Qween!

11:29.120 --> 11:31.540
Yas, Qween.
Be nice.

11:31.540 --> 11:34.330
It's this or risk getting
date-raped at a straight bar.

11:34.330 --> 11:35.710
Do you see
what I'm talking about now?

11:35.710 --> 11:38.080
That is what getting married
does to people.

11:38.080 --> 11:39.250
Why would we do that
to ourselves?

11:39.250 --> 11:40.670
Because
we love each other?

11:40.670 --> 11:43.170
We don't need to get married
to prove that.

11:43.170 --> 11:45.500
It just --
It feels forced and --

11:45.500 --> 11:48.170
Hetero-normative
and blah, blah, blah, blah.

11:48.170 --> 11:50.250
[ Cellphone beeps ]
I've been hearing this speech
for over a month now,

11:50.250 --> 11:52.540
so why don't we
just cut to the chase?

11:52.540 --> 11:55.580
Say yes.

11:55.580 --> 11:56.880
Or maybe I'll dump you
before that

11:56.880 --> 11:58.330
for always looking
at your phone.

11:58.330 --> 12:00.830
It's Annalise.

12:00.830 --> 12:03.790
She's making all of us get
dinner with her tomorrow night.

12:03.790 --> 12:06.330
Oh, she is?

12:06.330 --> 12:08.620
Oh. By "all of us,"
you mean everyone but me.

12:08.620 --> 12:09.750
Be relieved.

12:09.750 --> 12:11.380
I know
how you can get out of it.

12:11.380 --> 12:13.830
We go to Vegas and elope.

12:13.830 --> 12:15.330
This time tomorrow,
we could be

12:15.330 --> 12:17.420
screaming our married heads off
at Britney.

12:17.420 --> 12:19.580
I think I'd rather get dinner
with Annalise.

12:19.580 --> 12:21.580
[ Chuckling ]
You're such a bitch.

12:25.040 --> 12:30.460
[ Cheering ]

12:33.290 --> 12:36.040
Desmond: I should've
put this stuff away earlier.

12:36.040 --> 12:38.830
'Cause you knew I was coming?
[ Chuckles ]

12:38.830 --> 12:42.330
I hoped.

12:42.330 --> 12:43.670
Can I say something
you're not going to like?

12:43.670 --> 12:46.540
No.
Too bad.

12:46.540 --> 12:49.620
Everything about you,

12:49.620 --> 12:54.210
your eyes, your skin,
the way you carry yourself...

12:54.210 --> 12:56.170
I feel very lucky
you're here.

13:21.250 --> 13:22.960
Mm.

13:22.960 --> 13:24.380
[ Both moan ]

13:24.380 --> 13:26.580
Sorry.
It's okay.

13:26.580 --> 13:29.620
[ Both grunt ]

13:29.620 --> 13:31.250
[ Both breathing heavily ]

13:31.250 --> 13:33.540
[ Cellphone rings ]
My bad.

13:33.540 --> 13:37.540
Huh?
Just one second.
[ Grunts ]

13:39.960 --> 13:42.120
Don't move.

13:42.120 --> 13:45.500
Hey, CeCe!

13:45.500 --> 13:47.750
Oh, hell no.

13:50.250 --> 13:51.790
Yeah. Thanks for calling,
all right?

13:51.790 --> 13:53.500
Talk to you later.

13:53.500 --> 13:56.000
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no.

13:56.000 --> 13:59.040
That was rude.
It's rude for CeCe.
You do you.

13:59.040 --> 14:00.670
CeCe's my daughter.
She lives in L.A.

14:00.670 --> 14:02.830
I make her call every night
when she gets home.

14:02.830 --> 14:05.250
Look, we can call her together
if you want.

14:05.250 --> 14:06.920
But it might be
kinda awkward.

14:06.920 --> 14:09.880
[ Chuckles ]
Come here. Come on.

14:09.880 --> 14:12.330
Let's do this.

14:12.330 --> 14:13.620
Mm.

14:13.620 --> 14:17.710
[ Moaning ]

14:17.710 --> 14:19.040
No.

14:21.710 --> 14:23.460
Wait a second.

14:23.460 --> 14:26.580
We can go slower
if that's what you want.

14:26.580 --> 14:27.620
Bonnie.

14:27.620 --> 14:29.670
My name's Annalise.

14:31.880 --> 14:35.540
[ Bell jingles ]

14:42.880 --> 14:44.620
[ Bell jingles ]

14:54.920 --> 14:58.500
♪♪

14:58.500 --> 15:01.460
Anna Mae?
Anna Mae, wake up!

15:01.460 --> 15:03.710
Anna Mae, wake up.
The house is on fire.

15:03.710 --> 15:05.620
Mama?
The house is on fire.
Get up.

15:05.620 --> 15:07.500
He fell off drunk.
Daddy?

15:07.500 --> 15:10.420
No, Clyde!
And I lit him up.

15:10.420 --> 15:12.580
The house is on fire.

15:12.580 --> 15:14.960
We're gonna burn up
if we don't get out of here!

15:14.960 --> 15:18.580
Anna Mae!
Come on, come on, come on.

15:18.580 --> 15:19.710
Come on!

15:19.710 --> 15:22.120
Anna Mae,
the house is on fire.

15:22.120 --> 15:23.580
The house is not on fire.

15:23.580 --> 15:25.330
It is!
You're confused.

15:25.330 --> 15:26.880
If we don't get out of here,
we're gonna burn up.

15:26.880 --> 15:29.500
Anna Mae!
Clyde is dead!
He's dead, Mama.

15:29.500 --> 15:32.710
This is just the dementia.
You understand?

15:32.710 --> 15:41.420
♪♪

15:41.420 --> 15:49.830
♪♪

15:49.830 --> 15:58.290
♪♪

16:02.670 --> 16:05.040
[ Mattress whirring ]
Oh, my God.

16:05.040 --> 16:07.540
Oh, my body is in love.

16:07.540 --> 16:09.380
It's the kinda bed
you can spend all day in, right?

16:09.380 --> 16:10.790
Ohh.

16:10.790 --> 16:14.540
Excuse me, um, what's your most,
uh, durable mattress?

16:14.540 --> 16:17.750
'Cause my girlfriend here and I,
we're very much in love

16:17.750 --> 16:20.420
and, as you can probably tell,
we're very active.
Asher.

16:20.420 --> 16:22.790
So we need a bed
that can handle our once,

16:22.790 --> 16:26.540
sometimes twice-a-night visits
to pound town, just...

16:26.540 --> 16:28.830
[ Chuckles ]

16:28.830 --> 16:30.960
Give us a minute.
No prob.

16:30.960 --> 16:33.080
Hmm, thanks.
Bye, Chad.

16:37.580 --> 16:38.960
[ Grunts ]

16:38.960 --> 16:41.330
Threatened much?

16:41.330 --> 16:45.170
Bae is brilliant,
powerful, and hawt.

16:45.170 --> 16:48.540
It is my job
to be threatened.

16:48.540 --> 16:50.250
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Did you just toot?

16:50.250 --> 16:52.880
Ah! It's my phone.

16:52.880 --> 16:55.080
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:57.290 --> 16:58.750
Well, that's good news.

16:58.750 --> 17:00.290
How do you know?

17:00.290 --> 17:03.330
Haywood's like
4 dollar signs on Yelp.

17:03.330 --> 17:05.380
She wouldn't take us there
unless she had money coming in,

17:05.380 --> 17:06.540
which means
they didn't disbar her.

17:06.540 --> 17:08.250
Or she doesn't want us
making a scene

17:08.250 --> 17:10.000
when she delivers
terrible news.

17:10.000 --> 17:14.540
Like Denver
re-opened his investigation.

17:14.540 --> 17:16.710
She's throwing us
a last supper.

17:16.710 --> 17:17.880
Or she misses us.

17:17.880 --> 17:20.710
Baby, she's dead inside.

17:20.710 --> 17:22.670
She misses no one.

17:22.670 --> 17:25.620
[ Sighs ]

17:28.290 --> 17:30.790
Why does she have to ruin
everything?

17:33.040 --> 17:34.960
Wait till I move.
Ophelia: Okay.

17:34.960 --> 17:36.580
All right, Mama.

17:36.580 --> 17:38.330
-All right.
-Okay, Mama.

17:43.380 --> 17:45.210
[ Ophelia grunts ]

17:54.830 --> 17:56.420
There you go.

18:10.170 --> 18:12.790
♪ Little boy,
little girl? ♪

18:12.790 --> 18:16.000
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

18:16.000 --> 18:18.750
♪ Did you get any eggs? ♪

18:18.750 --> 18:20.710
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

18:20.710 --> 18:23.250
♪ Did you bring me mine? ♪

18:23.250 --> 18:26.540
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

18:26.540 --> 18:30.250
Bessie Jones.
Don't you remember?

18:30.250 --> 18:33.460
You and me
and -- and Celestine,

18:33.460 --> 18:38.120
we sang that every night
before you went to bed.

18:38.120 --> 18:40.880
♪ Did you bring me mine? ♪

18:40.880 --> 18:43.710
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

18:43.710 --> 18:45.580
♪ Then, shoo... ♪

18:45.580 --> 18:49.420
Both:
♪ Shoo, shoo, Turkey ♪

18:49.420 --> 18:53.670
♪ Throw your feathers
way off yonder ♪

18:53.670 --> 18:57.710
♪ Shoo, shoo, shoo, Turkey ♪

18:57.710 --> 19:01.960
♪ Throw your feathers
way off yonder ♪

19:01.960 --> 19:04.960
[ Both laugh ]

19:04.960 --> 19:06.830
See?

19:06.830 --> 19:10.080
I haven't lost
my whole mind.

19:10.080 --> 19:11.880
Not yet.

19:13.790 --> 19:15.580
[ Sniffles ]

19:20.710 --> 19:22.920
We'll go tomorrow.

19:22.920 --> 19:26.620
Hmm?

19:26.620 --> 19:29.290
The nursery home.

19:29.290 --> 19:32.000
We'll take a look around
tomorrow.

19:36.170 --> 19:37.960
[ Bessie Jones' "Shoo Turkey"
plays ]
♪ Little girl, little boy? ♪

19:37.960 --> 19:39.040
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

19:39.040 --> 19:40.960
♪ Well, did you go down town? ♪

19:40.960 --> 19:42.250
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

19:42.250 --> 19:44.120
♪ Well, did you get any eggs? ♪

19:44.120 --> 19:45.500
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

19:45.500 --> 19:47.120
♪ Well,
did you bring them home? ♪

19:47.120 --> 19:48.420
♪ Yes, ma'am ♪

19:48.420 --> 19:51.620
♪ Now, shoo, shoo, shoo,
Turkey ♪

19:51.620 --> 19:53.460
♪ Throw your feather
way yonder ♪

19:53.460 --> 19:56.710
Irene: The Acacia campus
has been open for over 20 years.

19:56.710 --> 19:59.380
The layout
is easy to navigate.

19:59.380 --> 20:02.000
There's 24-hour access
to specialist nurses

20:02.000 --> 20:03.420
and structured activities

20:03.420 --> 20:05.790
which we have designed
specifically

20:05.790 --> 20:08.210
for patients suffering
from memory loss.

20:08.210 --> 20:11.620
You've found
our photo collection.

20:11.620 --> 20:16.250
Our residents like reminders
of the good old days.

20:16.250 --> 20:17.960
Whose good old days?

20:17.960 --> 20:21.380
Oh, Mama,
look at the garden.
Yes.

20:21.380 --> 20:23.250
Do you know
how much this place costs?

20:23.250 --> 20:24.620
Best facility
in the state.

20:24.620 --> 20:27.290
$5,000 a month.

20:27.290 --> 20:28.540
Meanwhile it costs nothing

20:28.540 --> 20:30.540
for me to take care of her
in our own house.

20:30.540 --> 20:32.380
You mean the house she tried
to burn down last night?

20:32.380 --> 20:33.330
I can handle whatever care
she needs.

20:33.330 --> 20:34.420
That's all I'm saying.

20:34.420 --> 20:36.000
You couldn't handle her
when you were young.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.710
What makes you think
you can do it now?
I'm a better man now.

20:37.710 --> 20:39.540
You're no better
than the day you left her.

20:39.540 --> 20:40.670
Hush. We are not gonna
be the ratchet family

20:40.670 --> 20:42.000
fighting in public.
Mama was so desperate,

20:42.000 --> 20:43.500
she had to ask Uncle Clyde
to move in with us,

20:43.500 --> 20:44.920
and we all know
how that turned out.

20:44.920 --> 20:46.880
It always comes back to that
with you, don't it?

20:46.880 --> 20:48.420
This is about that.

20:48.420 --> 20:51.040
Even last night, that's
the memory Mama can't escape!

20:51.040 --> 20:53.000
Only 'cause you're here!
What did you say?

20:53.000 --> 20:55.710
I'm begging you.
You think she goes
through these spells about Clyde

20:55.710 --> 20:57.250
when you're not around?

20:57.250 --> 20:59.540
That's you stirring up
these memories.

20:59.540 --> 21:03.880
You're not too grown that
I can't still whip your ass.

21:03.880 --> 21:06.960
Quiet!
You're in these people's homes.

21:06.960 --> 21:08.750
You know better than that.

21:08.750 --> 21:11.330
And God knows
I taught you better.

21:11.330 --> 21:13.420
So now get it together!

21:13.420 --> 21:16.710
Humiliating me in public,
for shame.

21:21.120 --> 21:22.460
There's free parking,
Wi-Fi.

21:22.460 --> 21:24.040
Put a nice stencil here
on the window --

21:24.040 --> 21:27.580
Keating,
Winterbottom, Delfino.

21:30.080 --> 21:30.960
Frank --

21:30.960 --> 21:32.080
Relax.

21:32.080 --> 21:33.330
I know
she still hates me.

21:33.330 --> 21:35.830
I just figured
she needs a new office.

21:35.830 --> 21:37.710
She hasn't even gotten
her license back yet.

21:37.710 --> 21:38.580
You're gonna win it back.

21:38.580 --> 21:41.120
Maybe.

21:41.120 --> 21:44.000
Still, we can't afford
a place this nice.

21:44.000 --> 21:48.460
I got that covered.

21:48.460 --> 21:50.000
The suitcase money?

21:50.000 --> 21:52.830
It'd be a shame if nothing good
ever came of it.

21:52.830 --> 21:57.210
That is not the way to get
Annalise to forgive you, Frank.

22:01.960 --> 22:03.380
You busy tomorrow night?

22:03.380 --> 22:05.120
My mom's cooking
chicken parm.

22:07.080 --> 22:08.710
I got plans.

22:08.710 --> 22:11.170
Hot date?

22:11.170 --> 22:12.710
Annalise
is having a dinner.

22:12.710 --> 22:15.620
So it is a hot date.

22:15.620 --> 22:18.000
The kids will be there,
too.

22:22.790 --> 22:24.290
I'll win her back.

22:24.290 --> 22:25.750
Just give me time.

22:25.750 --> 22:33.040
♪♪

22:33.040 --> 22:34.330
Celestine: He's wrong.

22:34.330 --> 22:35.670
Stop.

22:35.670 --> 22:36.920
I'm just saying,

22:36.920 --> 22:40.080
whatever happened last night
wasn't triggered by you.

22:40.080 --> 22:41.580
Really?

22:41.580 --> 22:43.750
So Mama walks around talking
about burning down the house

22:43.750 --> 22:44.750
even when I'm not here?

22:44.750 --> 22:46.580
I'm a nurse, okay?

22:46.580 --> 22:49.670
I know how dementia works,
and that ain't it.

22:54.790 --> 22:57.120
I don't have the money,
Celestine.

22:57.120 --> 22:58.250
What?

23:04.460 --> 23:07.790
Sam's sister's
suing me for the house.

23:07.790 --> 23:09.880
It froze
the insurance payout.

23:14.250 --> 23:17.170
That's okay.

23:17.170 --> 23:19.250
We've still got our jobs.

23:19.250 --> 23:22.040
I don't know if that's true
anymore.

23:22.040 --> 23:26.170
They found alcohol in my blood
when I was arrested.

23:26.170 --> 23:28.880
I might be disbarred.

23:28.880 --> 23:31.250
Because you had
a little too much to drink?

23:31.250 --> 23:34.000
I was on probation
at the time.

23:34.000 --> 23:35.580
For what?

23:37.830 --> 23:39.580
Drinking.

23:39.580 --> 23:47.120
♪♪

23:47.120 --> 23:51.170
I'd be drinking too
if I had your life.

23:51.170 --> 23:55.960
♪♪

23:58.210 --> 24:01.540
Where's Daddy?

24:01.540 --> 24:04.750
Hardware store.

24:04.750 --> 24:07.540
Pretty soon enough I won't be
able to use the restroom

24:07.540 --> 24:09.170
without setting off a bell.

24:09.170 --> 24:11.080
[ Chuckles ]

24:15.290 --> 24:17.540
What do you want, Mama?

24:17.540 --> 24:20.460
Hmm?

24:20.460 --> 24:22.620
Where do you want to live?

24:22.620 --> 24:25.040
Would you rather stay here
with Daddy?

24:25.040 --> 24:26.830
Doesn't matter
what I want.

24:26.830 --> 24:30.120
Well, that's the only thing
that matters.

24:30.120 --> 24:32.670
It doesn't.

24:32.670 --> 24:35.620
Mama, I'm not gonna be
able to leave here

24:35.620 --> 24:37.880
if I know
you're upset with me.

24:37.880 --> 24:40.710
Anna Mae,

24:40.710 --> 24:44.290
I want you to hear me...

24:44.290 --> 24:47.170
and I want you
to hear me well...

24:49.670 --> 24:52.420
...because you're the one
who's confused right now.

24:56.120 --> 24:59.080
I'm going away.

25:03.000 --> 25:05.880
You know it.

25:05.880 --> 25:09.080
I know it.

25:09.080 --> 25:12.620
My mind's going.

25:12.620 --> 25:15.540
So whether I live or die,
it's not about me.

25:15.540 --> 25:17.380
It's what you want,
your father wants,

25:17.380 --> 25:19.420
what your sister wants.
That is not true.

25:19.420 --> 25:21.670
I mean,
listen to you right now.

25:21.670 --> 25:24.960
You're clear-headed,
sometimes more than any of us.

25:24.960 --> 25:27.750
And next time
you come to visit?

25:27.750 --> 25:29.880
And the time after that?

25:33.290 --> 25:36.500
Anna Mae, what happened to you
is not right.

25:40.210 --> 25:42.290
I've had my share of loss,
too.

25:45.620 --> 25:47.540
No one...

25:49.790 --> 25:52.250
...my sweet baby girl,

25:52.250 --> 25:57.920
should lose
as much as you have lost.

25:57.920 --> 26:00.330
What Mama's trying to do

26:00.330 --> 26:03.620
is to protect you
from losing any more.

26:03.620 --> 26:08.960
♪♪

26:08.960 --> 26:12.790
But it's happening.

26:12.790 --> 26:15.170
You're losing me.

26:18.540 --> 26:23.210
You're losing me,
and there's nothing...

26:23.210 --> 26:26.920
you can do to stop it
from happening.

26:26.920 --> 26:32.790
The best thing for us to do
is to prepare ourselves

26:32.790 --> 26:37.920
so it won't be
a surprise.

26:42.500 --> 26:44.290
[ Voice breaking ]
I can't.

26:46.880 --> 26:48.540
Don't worry.

26:51.750 --> 26:54.250
I'll stay
as long as I can.

26:54.250 --> 27:00.120
I promise you I will hold on
to me for as long as I can,

27:00.120 --> 27:03.960
and what I want
is for you...

27:03.960 --> 27:07.040
to hold on to you too.

27:07.040 --> 27:12.380
♪♪

27:12.380 --> 27:17.670
♪♪

27:17.670 --> 27:20.080
Man: Today we begin
the disbarment proceedings

27:20.080 --> 27:21.580
for
Attorney Annalise Keating.

27:21.580 --> 27:24.120
This hearing arises
out of a violation

27:24.120 --> 27:26.380
of a previously
imposed probation

27:26.380 --> 27:29.670
that prohibited Ms. Keating
from using any drugs or alcohol.

27:34.170 --> 27:38.080
She can't leave the room
if she doesn't have a key.

27:38.080 --> 27:39.830
I know
it's not ideal but --

27:39.830 --> 27:43.210
This one's on you.

27:43.210 --> 27:45.330
If she hurts herself
or someone else,

27:45.330 --> 27:47.210
it's your job
to take care of her.

27:51.670 --> 27:54.380
'Cause if I find out that
you've had one too many drinks,

27:54.380 --> 27:57.620
if you slept
through that damn bell...

27:57.620 --> 28:04.040
♪♪

28:04.040 --> 28:07.000
Just keep her safe.

28:07.000 --> 28:12.000
♪♪

28:12.000 --> 28:15.460
I give up, okay?
Enough.

28:18.580 --> 28:22.250
I'm sorry...

28:22.250 --> 28:24.830
for what Clyde did to you.

28:24.830 --> 28:32.790
♪♪

28:32.790 --> 28:35.120
[ Inhales sharply ]

28:35.120 --> 28:37.920
I'll text you
when my plane lands.

28:37.920 --> 28:42.540
♪ You need me ♪

28:42.540 --> 28:44.250
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

28:44.250 --> 28:45.960
Man: Police reports state

28:45.960 --> 28:48.080
Ms. Keating violated
this probation

28:48.080 --> 28:49.500
on the night
of November 3rd.

28:54.040 --> 28:56.880
♪ I'm here ♪
On the night of her arrest,

28:56.880 --> 29:00.000
Ms. Keating was found
to be intoxicated.

29:00.000 --> 29:04.250
Lab tests showed
a blood alcohol content of 0.15,

29:04.250 --> 29:06.500
thereby triggering
this disbarment hearing.

29:06.500 --> 29:07.960
We'll now hear arguments

29:07.960 --> 29:10.790
on why this Board
should not disbar Ms. Keating.

29:10.790 --> 29:13.710
Ms. Winterbottom, has counsel
prepared a statement?

29:13.710 --> 29:14.580
We have.

29:16.790 --> 29:19.120
It's our firm belief
that Ms. Keating's lab results

29:19.120 --> 29:20.880
on the night in question
are unreliable

29:20.880 --> 29:22.710
as they may have been
tampered with

29:22.710 --> 29:24.960
by the A.D.A. handling
the case.
Annalise: Bonnie.

29:24.960 --> 29:27.500
The allegations
are correct.

29:27.500 --> 29:30.250
Annalise.
I was drunk that night.
It's true.

29:30.250 --> 29:32.040
My house burned down,
and as a result,

29:32.040 --> 29:34.000
I lost
everything that I owned.

29:34.000 --> 29:37.460
None of it matters, though,
because a life was lost too.

29:37.460 --> 29:42.750
My student, Wes Gibbins,
took his life at my home.

29:42.750 --> 29:44.250
And I wake up every day

29:44.250 --> 29:46.580
knowing that a young man
with so much potential,

29:46.580 --> 29:47.830
who needed me the most,

29:47.830 --> 29:51.080
died because
I decided to take a drink.

29:51.080 --> 29:52.750
I have not had a drink
since.

29:52.750 --> 29:54.750
I've worked very hard
to stay sober,

29:54.750 --> 29:56.540
and I will continue
to do so

29:56.540 --> 29:58.750
by going to AA meetings,
seeing a counselor.

29:58.750 --> 30:00.670
Ms. Keating, the conditions
of your probation

30:00.670 --> 30:02.670
were that you could
and would not drink again.

30:02.670 --> 30:04.710
I know.
You agreed, to my face,

30:04.710 --> 30:07.170
that we were to disbar you
if you relapsed.

30:07.170 --> 30:09.210
And if you do that,
I will have nothing.

30:09.210 --> 30:10.540
I've lost everything.

30:10.540 --> 30:13.290
My home, my husband,
my reputation, my teaching.

30:13.290 --> 30:14.750
It's all gone.

30:14.750 --> 30:17.830
And you're deciding to take
the only thing that I have left.

30:17.830 --> 30:20.330
Now, I understand that
you have the right to do this,

30:20.330 --> 30:23.750
and it's all on me, but I am
standing here begging you --

30:23.750 --> 30:25.880
begging --

30:25.880 --> 30:28.290
to take mercy on me.

30:28.290 --> 30:32.710
Please, please,
just give me one more chance.

30:39.330 --> 30:41.330
Laurel: Hey.
Sorry I'm late.

30:41.330 --> 30:43.420
My Uber driver
put in the wrong address.

30:43.420 --> 30:45.880
Oh, what's this?

30:45.880 --> 30:47.500
She won't tell us.

30:47.500 --> 30:49.290
I'll tell you,
but we should order first.

30:49.290 --> 30:50.120
Sit.

30:52.750 --> 30:54.540
Just to be clear, is there a
limit to how much we can order?

30:54.540 --> 30:56.290
Because I'm thinking
about getting the rib-eye
for two, for one.

30:56.290 --> 30:57.620
-Order whatever you want.
-Great.

30:57.620 --> 31:00.080
I'm gonna have lamb chops.
Now can we open them?

31:00.080 --> 31:03.580
After dinner.
I think that we've had enough
suspense to last a lifetime.

31:03.580 --> 31:05.080
So why don't you
just tell us why we're here?

31:10.580 --> 31:12.580
I had my disciplinary hearing
today.

31:12.580 --> 31:14.960
Oh, my God.
They disbarred you, didn't they?

31:14.960 --> 31:16.620
Just let her finish.

31:16.620 --> 31:18.330
I won.

31:18.330 --> 31:20.080
I get to practice again
right away.

31:22.040 --> 31:23.670
For real?
Yeah, but, uh --

31:23.670 --> 31:25.250
So this is a celebration
then?

31:25.250 --> 31:26.880
Waiter, more champers
in here, waiter!

31:26.880 --> 31:28.580
Wait.
Does this mean you can teach?

31:28.580 --> 31:31.120
Well, I think stepping foot
on campus is not a good idea.

31:31.120 --> 31:32.250
No, that's just
letting them win!

31:32.250 --> 31:33.540
Or she just needs
a breather.

31:33.540 --> 31:34.830
We need another glass
for Laurel.

31:34.830 --> 31:36.580
No, it's fine.

31:36.580 --> 31:39.170
AK said we can eat and drink
as much as we want.

31:39.170 --> 31:43.120
I can't.
I'm having the baby, so...

31:46.750 --> 31:49.920
I thought about it, and...

31:49.920 --> 31:52.040
I want to have it.

31:52.040 --> 31:55.000
I'm due in 5 months,
which is soon.

31:55.000 --> 31:58.540
That's crazy soon,
but, yeah, that's my news.

31:58.540 --> 32:01.670
So it's a double celebration
then.

32:01.670 --> 32:03.330
Not only is the band
getting back together,

32:03.330 --> 32:04.420
but the band's
gonna have a baby.

32:04.420 --> 32:06.000
Michaela: Do you know
if it's a boy or girl?

32:06.000 --> 32:07.580
But I get to help pick the name,
right?

32:07.580 --> 32:09.170
Connor: Well, obviously
the child's "guncles"

32:09.170 --> 32:10.120
will be in charge
of picking the name.

32:10.120 --> 32:11.710
Bonnie: You okay?
Listen.

32:11.710 --> 32:13.380
Does the fact that you're
calling yourselves "guncles"

32:13.380 --> 32:14.460
mean you've said yes?

32:14.460 --> 32:16.250
-Yes to what?
-Oh, Oliver proposed.

32:16.250 --> 32:18.330
You need to say yes already,
scaredy cat.

32:18.330 --> 32:21.790
You didn't let me finish.

32:21.790 --> 32:25.080
Inside the envelopes
are recommendation letters.

32:25.080 --> 32:26.960
I wrote one
for each of you.

32:26.960 --> 32:28.000
That's so sweet.

32:28.000 --> 32:30.670
I'm letting you go.

32:33.620 --> 32:37.420
Look at us.

32:37.420 --> 32:40.830
We're here,
at this restaurant.

32:40.830 --> 32:44.080
We've been given
a second chance.

32:44.080 --> 32:46.290
We don't need each other
anymore.

32:46.290 --> 32:48.920
So it's time we went
our separate ways.

32:48.920 --> 32:52.080
Remember who you were
before you met me,

32:52.080 --> 32:54.250
why you went to law school.

32:54.250 --> 32:55.830
I came here to be you.

32:55.830 --> 32:57.500
And look how that
turned out.

32:57.500 --> 33:00.710
Look.

33:00.710 --> 33:02.540
Who isn't at this table?

33:02.540 --> 33:04.330
[ Sniffles ]

33:04.330 --> 33:05.460
And I know you think about him
every day.

33:05.460 --> 33:06.710
So do I.

33:06.710 --> 33:08.290
And I'm the reason
why he's gone.

33:08.290 --> 33:10.380
No, that was Denver
and the Mahoneys.

33:10.380 --> 33:12.330
-We don't know that anymore.
-Since when?

33:12.330 --> 33:14.120
Laurel's right.

33:14.120 --> 33:17.080
I'm not gonna blame anyone
for what happened anymore.

33:17.080 --> 33:18.960
It was me.
I ruined him.

33:18.960 --> 33:22.580
But I'm not gonna ruin
all of you.

33:27.170 --> 33:29.330
Is that it?

33:29.330 --> 33:30.620
Are we free to go?

33:30.620 --> 33:31.880
Laurel.

33:31.880 --> 33:37.920
♪♪

33:37.920 --> 33:38.830
Good night.

33:42.250 --> 33:44.620
What the hell
is wrong with you?
Michaela, calm down.

33:44.620 --> 33:46.330
Do not defend her,
you pathetic little sycophant!

33:46.330 --> 33:48.120
We are in a relationship,
all of us,

33:48.120 --> 33:49.500
whether
you like it or not,

33:49.500 --> 33:51.460
so you don't get to unilaterally
decide when it's over.

33:51.460 --> 33:53.460
Seriously.
We're like the Corleones.

33:53.460 --> 33:54.880
We got to stick together.

33:54.880 --> 33:56.750
Connor: Why are you both
complaining?

33:56.750 --> 33:59.880
This is exactly what we begged
for this entire time.

33:59.880 --> 34:00.920
I want to be free of her

34:00.920 --> 34:02.420
once she's upheld
her end of the deal!

34:02.420 --> 34:04.330
Michaela.
We're halfway through
law school.

34:04.330 --> 34:06.000
No stupid
recommendation letter

34:06.000 --> 34:08.000
is going to make up
for my embarrassing GPA

34:08.000 --> 34:10.120
or the fact that we're pariahs
on that campus!

34:10.120 --> 34:13.710
Only you can fix that!
We're no good
for each other.

34:17.330 --> 34:19.170
Wow.

34:23.000 --> 34:25.420
Have a terrible
rest of your life.

34:25.420 --> 34:31.620
♪♪

34:31.620 --> 34:35.580
Maybe next time maybe don't
invite people to a fancy dinner

34:35.580 --> 34:36.710
to dump them.

34:36.710 --> 34:42.330
♪♪

34:42.330 --> 34:47.960
♪♪

34:47.960 --> 34:49.580
Thank you.

34:49.580 --> 34:56.080
♪♪

34:56.080 --> 35:02.580
♪♪

35:02.580 --> 35:05.580
They'll understand
eventually

35:05.580 --> 35:08.210
that
this is good for them.

35:08.210 --> 35:16.000
♪♪

35:16.000 --> 35:19.330
No.

35:19.330 --> 35:21.710
You don't have to do this.

35:21.710 --> 35:24.380
Annalise.

35:24.380 --> 35:32.920
♪♪

35:37.500 --> 35:38.920
A daily newspaper
is complimentary.

35:38.920 --> 35:40.960
And we offer a host of other
amenities for all of our guests.

35:44.080 --> 35:48.420
This is our fully-furnished
1-bedroom suite.

35:55.790 --> 35:59.330
As for your neighbors,
we've got lots of single men.

35:59.330 --> 36:01.710
And women, too,
depending on your flavor.

36:01.710 --> 36:03.250
Most guests pay weekly,

36:03.250 --> 36:05.790
but we give a discount
for a monthly rate.

36:05.790 --> 36:10.420
I'll take it
for the month.

36:10.420 --> 36:12.000
I'll be right back
with some forms to sign.

36:18.540 --> 36:21.620
[ Cage the Elephant's
"Cold Cold Cold" plays ]

36:21.620 --> 36:23.500
Annalise: As a member
of the Pennsylvania Bar

36:23.500 --> 36:25.420
and former professor
at Middleton Law School,

36:25.420 --> 36:28.210
it is with great pleasure
I write this recommendation

36:28.210 --> 36:30.710
on behalf of one
of the most impressive interns

36:30.710 --> 36:34.040
to work at my firm --
Laurel Castillo.

36:34.040 --> 36:37.750
Upon our first meeting, I
underestimated Ms. Castillo.

36:37.750 --> 36:40.920
I took her quiet demeanor
as a sign of weakness

36:40.920 --> 36:42.960
instead of what it is --

36:42.960 --> 36:46.580
a clear, unwavering
sense of self.

36:46.580 --> 36:49.830
Ms. Castillo knows who she is
and what she wants.

36:49.830 --> 36:51.330
This will serve her well

36:51.330 --> 36:53.960
when the vagaries of the law
would lead most astray.

36:53.960 --> 36:58.170
Mr. Millstone refuses to be
defined by his family name.

36:58.170 --> 36:59.960
Instead,
he forges his own path,

36:59.960 --> 37:02.920
guided by his compassion
and strong sense of teamwork.

37:02.920 --> 37:05.040
Ms. Pratt is fearless,

37:05.040 --> 37:07.920
possessing a confidence
I wish I had at her age.

37:07.920 --> 37:09.120
Asher: I'll show you mine
if you show me yours.

37:09.120 --> 37:11.000
[ Inhales deeply ]

37:11.000 --> 37:13.960
No.

37:13.960 --> 37:18.000
Come on, I'm sure yours is way
more complimentary than mine.

37:18.000 --> 37:23.000
No. I mean no more giving
that bitch our time or energy.

37:23.000 --> 37:24.620
We're finally free of her.

37:24.620 --> 37:25.960
We have to use it
to our advantage.

37:25.960 --> 37:27.880
Get amazing internships

37:27.880 --> 37:31.500
and become the Michelle and...
White Barack we're meant to be.

37:31.500 --> 37:34.000
Come on, come on, come on.

37:34.000 --> 37:35.880
It's beast mode time!

37:35.880 --> 37:37.500
Say it with me!

37:37.500 --> 37:38.420
Beast mode?

37:38.420 --> 37:40.710
Not "beast mode?"

37:40.710 --> 37:42.920
Beast. Mode.

37:42.920 --> 37:45.040
Beast mode!
Yeah!

37:45.040 --> 37:46.620
Beast mode!
That's
what I'm talking about!

37:46.620 --> 37:49.210
Okay, uh, what exactly does
that mean in this situation?

37:49.210 --> 37:52.120
Get your laptop,
fix your résumé.

37:52.120 --> 37:53.330
It boggles one's mind

37:53.330 --> 37:55.420
how a young person
like Ms. Pratt

37:55.420 --> 37:57.830
can possess such poise
and self-reliance.

37:57.830 --> 38:00.460
The more the odds are stacked
against Mr. Walsh,

38:00.460 --> 38:01.670
the more he fights.

38:01.670 --> 38:03.500
Any client would be lucky

38:03.500 --> 38:05.540
to have him on their side.
"Any client would be lucky
to have him on their side."

38:05.540 --> 38:07.420
She's just blowing smoke
up our asses

38:07.420 --> 38:09.120
so that we don't bother her
again.

38:09.120 --> 38:11.960
She didn't even tell me
I was fired,

38:11.960 --> 38:13.880
let alone write a letter.

38:13.880 --> 38:15.380
Combine that with the fact

38:15.380 --> 38:17.380
that you still won't respond
to my marriage proposal,

38:17.380 --> 38:19.750
my self-esteem's
really taken a blow.

38:19.750 --> 38:21.750
Not the good kind.

38:21.750 --> 38:24.000
[ Chuckles ]

38:24.000 --> 38:26.000
Of course
I want to get married.

38:26.000 --> 38:27.790
You do?
Yes!

38:27.790 --> 38:30.460
I want us to have kids

38:30.460 --> 38:35.000
and a house and a dog

38:35.000 --> 38:38.420
and grow old and die
within a week of each other.

38:38.420 --> 38:42.790
But I want to say yes because
we're in a good place,

38:42.790 --> 38:47.080
not -- not because you're afraid
that I'm going to jail

38:47.080 --> 38:49.540
or someone's
going to kill us,

38:49.540 --> 38:54.750
but because things
are normal and good

38:54.750 --> 38:59.460
and we're happy
just being boring old us.

38:59.460 --> 39:02.000
[ Chuckles ]

39:02.000 --> 39:04.960
For once, I want to do something
the right way.

39:08.960 --> 39:10.880
That's...

39:10.880 --> 39:13.170
the best rejection
I could've asked for.

39:17.670 --> 39:20.830
It's this personal growth
that gives me the confidence

39:20.830 --> 39:24.330
to say hire
Ms. Castillo immediately.

39:24.330 --> 39:26.620
She will work tirelessly
for you.

39:26.620 --> 39:32.710
[ Cellphone chimes ]
♪ And as the darkness falls,
it fills up both my eyes ♪

39:32.710 --> 39:38.580
♪ My life before me
like a flash in the night ♪

39:38.580 --> 39:44.540
♪ With my arms open wide ♪

39:44.540 --> 39:51.040
♪♪

39:51.040 --> 39:57.830
♪♪

39:57.830 --> 40:00.420
No matter what obstacles
stand in her way,

40:00.420 --> 40:02.670
no matter how hard
the challenge,

40:02.670 --> 40:07.620
Ms. Winterbottom is defined
by her sense of loyalty.

40:07.620 --> 40:10.170
Hey.

40:10.170 --> 40:11.460
What are you doing here?

40:11.460 --> 40:13.620
I've got
an appointment.

40:13.620 --> 40:14.620
With?

40:14.620 --> 40:16.750
[ Door opens ]

40:16.750 --> 40:18.420
Ms. Winterbottom?

40:18.420 --> 40:19.790
I'm ready for you.

40:19.790 --> 40:22.120
♪ Well, it's cold, cold, cold,
cold inside ♪

40:22.120 --> 40:24.250
♪ Darker in the day
than the dead of night ♪

40:24.250 --> 40:27.420
Annalise:
She stood by my side through
the worst times of my career.

40:27.420 --> 40:29.210
The pain of seeing her leave

40:29.210 --> 40:31.420
is softened
only by the knowledge

40:31.420 --> 40:35.960
that she is destined
for bigger and better things.

40:35.960 --> 40:39.120
Sincerely,
Annalise Keating, Esquire.

40:46.420 --> 40:49.290
Ms. Keating?

40:49.290 --> 40:50.120
You're late.

40:54.960 --> 40:57.880
So, this treatment
is court-ordered.

40:57.880 --> 40:59.960
For me to report favorably,

40:59.960 --> 41:02.620
do not show up late,
do not cancel,

41:02.620 --> 41:05.420
do not drink.

41:05.420 --> 41:07.460
Do you understand
these terms?

41:07.460 --> 41:09.380
Yes.

41:09.380 --> 41:10.580
Good.

41:10.580 --> 41:12.620
Normal to be nervous
your first time.

41:12.620 --> 41:14.710
I've been to therapy
before.

41:14.710 --> 41:18.710
Your nerves,
they're about something else?

41:18.710 --> 41:20.710
I...

41:20.710 --> 41:25.040
just want to get better.

41:25.040 --> 41:28.290
You showed up.

41:28.290 --> 41:29.750
That's a good start.

41:29.750 --> 41:36.620
♪ Doctor, look into my eyes ♪

41:36.620 --> 41:38.830
♪ I've been breathing air,
but there's no sign of life ♪

41:38.830 --> 41:41.290
Frank: Down here.

41:41.290 --> 41:42.540
How is she?
Still unconscious.

41:42.540 --> 41:44.670
A nurse said they found drugs
in her system.

41:44.670 --> 41:46.920
What drugs?
Woman: Page Dr. Lee!
Tell him she's waking up.

41:46.920 --> 41:52.960
♪♪

41:52.960 --> 41:57.380
-Hi.
-Frank?

41:57.380 --> 41:59.620
What is it?

42:02.620 --> 42:03.830
Frank?

42:03.830 --> 42:05.790
What happened, Frank?

42:05.790 --> 42:07.290
Where's the baby?

42:07.290 --> 42:08.500
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

42:08.500 --> 42:09.420
What happened?

42:09.420 --> 42:10.920
Everything's
gonna be all right.

42:10.920 --> 42:12.880
Where's the baby?
Laurel.

42:12.880 --> 42:14.500
Tell me where the baby is.
Shh, shh.

42:14.500 --> 42:15.920
Tell me where the baby is!
It's gonna be okay.

42:15.920 --> 42:17.540
Shh, shh.
Where's my baby?!

42:17.540 --> 42:20.290
Where's my baby?!
Tell me where my baby is!

42:20.290 --> 42:22.500
[ Shrieking ] Tell me!

42:29.580 --> 42:37.620
♪♪

42:37.620 --> 42:45.710
♪♪

42:45.710 --> 42:48.710
♪♪
